.TH "fc_fcp_send_data" 9 "fc_fcp_send_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_fcp_send_data \- Send SCSI data to a target
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fc_fcp_send_data
.BI "(struct fc_fcp_pkt *fsp "  ","
.BI "struct fc_seq *seq "  ","
.BI "size_t offset "  ","
.BI "size_t seq_blen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fsp" 12
The FCP packet the data is on
.IP "seq" 12
The sequence the data is to be sent on
.IP "offset" 12
The starting offset for this data request
.IP "seq_blen" 12
The burst length for this data request
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called after receiving a Transfer Ready data descriptor.
If the LLD is capable of sequence offload then send down the
seq_blen amount of data in single frame, otherwise send
multiple frames of the maximum frame payload supported by
the target port.
